  "bib_entries": {
    "8958038": {
      "title": "Use of polyethylene glycol to separate free and antibody-bound peptide hormones in radioimmunoassays",
      "abstract": "ABSTRACT Aqueous polyethylene glycol causes precipitation of antibody-bound peptide hormones labeled with radioactive iodine with little or no precipitation of free hormones. Based on this finding, a method of separation has been developed and applied to radioimmunoassays of insulin, parathyroid hormone, growth hormone and arginine vasopressin. The new method provides several advantages over the double-antibody precipitation method. It appears particularly valuable in immunoassays of substances of low molecular weight."
    }
  },
